verses.text:
As for their rings, they were so high that they were dreadful;
and their rings \add were\add* full of eyes round about them four.\f + \fr 1.18 
\ft and their rings: or, and their strakes\f*

Every one had four faces apiece, and every one four wings;
and the likeness of the hands of a man \add was\add* under their
wings.

Thus will I accomplish my wrath upon the wall, and upon them that have
daubed it with untempered \add morter\add*, and will say unto you, The
wall \add is\add* no \add more\add*, neither they that daubed it;

And I will set my face against that man, and will make him a
sign and a proverb, and I will cut him off from the midst of my people;
and ye shall know that I \add am\add* the \nd LORD\nd*.

How weak is thine heart, saith  the Lord \nd GOD\nd*, seeing thou
doest all these \add things\add*, the work of an imperious whorish
 woman;

And hath not oppressed any, \add but\add* hath restored to the
debtor his pledge, hath spoiled none by violence, hath given his
bread to the hungry, and hath covered the naked with a garment;

Son of man, set thy face toward the south, and drop \add thy
word\add* toward the south, and prophesy against the forest of the
south field;

¶ Therefore, O Aholibah, thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*; Behold, I will raise
up thy lovers against thee, from whom thy mind is alienated, and I will
bring them against thee on every side;

Thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*; Thou shalt drink of thy sister’s
cup deep and large: thou shalt be laughed to scorn and had in derision;
it containeth much.

And say unto the Ammonites, Hear the word of the Lord \nd GOD\nd*;
Thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*; Because thou saidst, Aha, against my
sanctuary, when it was profaned; and against the land of Israel,
when it was desolate; and against the house of Judah, when they went
into captivity;

¶ Thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*; Because that Moab and Seir
do say, Behold, the house of Judah \add is\add* like unto all the
heathen;

For thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*; When I shall make thee a
desolate city, like the cities that are not inhabited; when I shall bring
up the deep upon thee, and great waters shall cover thee;

And all that handle the oar, the mariners, \add and\add* all the
pilots of the sea, shall come down from their ships, they shall stand
upon the land;

Son of man, I have broken the arm of Pharaoh king of Egypt;
and, lo, it shall not be bound up to be healed, to put a roller to
bind it, to make it strong to hold the sword.

¶ Therefore thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*; Because thou hast lifted
up thyself in height, and he hath shot up his top among the thick
boughs, and his heart is lifted up in his height;

Therefore, O thou son of man, speak unto the house of Israel;
Thus ye speak, saying, If our transgressions and our sins \add be\add*
upon us, and we pine away in them, how should we then live?

Again, when I say unto the wicked, Thou shalt surely die;
if he turn from his sin, and do that which is lawful and right;\f + \fr 33.14 
\ft that…: Heb. judgment and justice\f*

\add If\add* the wicked restore the pledge, give again that he had
robbed, walk in the statutes of life, without committing iniquity;
he shall surely live, he shall not die.

Wherefore say unto them, Thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*;
Ye eat with the blood, and lift up your eyes toward your idols, and
shed blood: and shall ye possess the land?

And I will make them and the places round about my hill a
blessing; and I will cause the shower to come down in his season;
there shall be showers of blessing.

For in my jealousy \add and\add* in the fire of my wrath have I
spoken, Surely in that day there shall be a great shaking in the
land of Israel;

Therefore thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*; Now will I bring
again the captivity of Jacob, and have mercy upon the whole house
of Israel, and will be jealous for my holy name;

When I have brought them again from the people, and gathered
them out of their enemies’ lands, and am sanctified in them in the
sight of many nations;

And the arches thereof \add were\add* toward the utter court;
and palm trees \add were\add* upon the posts thereof: and the going
up to it \add had\add* eight steps.

And the arches thereof \add were\add* toward the outward court;
and palm trees \add were\add* upon the posts thereof, on this side, and on that side: and the going
up to it \add had\add* eight steps.

And the posts thereof \add were\add* toward the utter court;
and palm trees \add were\add* upon the posts thereof, on this side, and on that side: and the going
up to it \add had\add* eight steps.

So he measured the house, an hundred cubits long; and the separate
place, and the building, with the walls thereof, an hundred cubits
long;

And \add it was\add* made with cherubims and palm trees, so that a palm
tree \add was\add* between a cherub and a cherub; and \add every\add*
cherub had two faces;

And thou shalt say to the rebellious, \add even\add* to the
house of Israel, Thus saith the Lord \nd GOD\nd*; O ye house of Israel,
let it suffice you of all your abominations,

And so thou shalt do the seventh \add day\add* of the month
for every one that erreth, and for \add him that is\add* simple:
so shall ye reconcile the house.

Again he measured a thousand, and brought me through the waters;
the waters \add were\add* to the knees. Again he measured a thousand,
and brought me through; the waters \add were\add* to the loins.

And this \add shall be\add* the border of the land toward the
north side, from the great sea, the way of Hethlon, as men go to
Zedad;
